<TITLE> Ukrainian helicopter crashes in Black Sea, 19 dead </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 KIEV, April 28 (bdnews24.com/Reuters) - A Ukrainian helicopter struck an offshore drilling platform and crashed in the Black Sea on Monday, killing 19 people, the state energy company Naftogaz said. One survivor has been found but his condition was unknown, a company spokesman said. He said no one was hurt on the platform, which is operated by Naftogaz. "An Mi-8 helicopter with 20 people on board clipped the Tavrida platform with its tail rotor, and as a result 19 people died and one survived," another spokesman, Ilya Savin, said. The helicopter belonged to Naftogaz and was taking workers to the platform, local news reports said. An Mi-8 belonging to Ukraine's border guards crashed a month ago off an island in the Black Sea, killing 12 peopl
